  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification has been performed across inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity using Monte Carlo sampling (n=2000). We plan to extend with sensitivity analysis in a future revision to identify dominant input drivers, but no ranked sensitivity indices are available at this time.",
